subsection.def:
excavation
                    (挖掘處) means any opening, hole or trench
                executed in any road;

footway
                    (行人徑) means a pavement comprised in a road
                with a right of way on foot only;

kerb
                    (路邊石) means a border of stone, concrete or
                other rigid material formed at the edge of a carriageway;

roundabout
                    (迴旋處) means a road junction designed for the
                movement of traffic in one direction round a central island;

stud
                    (路釘) means a mark or device on a carriageway,
                whether or not projecting above the surface of the carriageway;

